  m_Name: Flexor_carpi_radialis_muscle.R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Flexor_carpi_radialis_muscle.R
  partName: Flexor carpi radialis muscle Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right flexor carpi radialis muscle occupies the medial region of the canine
    forearm and serves as an important flexor of the carpal joint. It originates
    from the humerus and extends distally to attach to the metacarpal area, enabling
    controlled bending of the wrist during movement.
  - This muscle contributes to forelimb stability, coordinated paw placement, and
    efficient weight distribution during walking, running, and jumping activities.
    Working alongside other forearm flexors, it supports smooth locomotion and shock
    absorption during ground contact. Proper function is vital for balanced forelimb
    mechanics.
